# App Shells

## Routes must stay thin

```tsx
'use client'; // web only, when re-exporting shared screens
export { LoginScreen as default } from '@app-template/app';
```

Do not add screen UI, forms, or business logic in route files.

## What belongs in apps (platform-specific)

- **Web:** `providers.tsx`, `lib/auth.tsx`, `lib/convex-client.ts`, OAuth pages (`/auth/google`, `/auth/apple`), API routes, `next.config.mjs`
- **Mobile:** `_layout.tsx`, `lib/auth.tsx`, `lib/convex.ts`, `app/auth/callback.tsx`, `lib/oauth.tsx`

## Mobile dev builds

Mobile uses **expo-dev-client**, not Expo Go. OAuth and native modules require a dev build with the app's bundle ID.

- First run: `cd apps/client-mobile && npx expo run:ios` (or `eas build --profile development`)
- Daily dev: `npm run dev:client:mobile` from repo root (Metro for dev client)
- Rebuild dev client when adding/changing native dependencies

## Auth wiring pattern

Apps create `AuthProvider` by calling `createAuthProvider(api, tokenStore)` from `@app-template/app` with the platform token store, then wrap the tree in `_layout` / `providers.tsx`.

## Safe area

Both shells must include `SafeAreaProvider` around the app tree (already in `_layout.tsx` / `providers.tsx`). Screen-level safe-area padding lives in `@app-template/app` (`Screen`, `AuthScreen`) — do not add inset logic in route files.

## User-facing errors

Platform routes and callbacks must never render `error.message` directly. Use `getUserFacingErrorMessage()` from `@app-template/app` — it maps backend `AppErrorCode` values to UI copy.

## Gluestack v5 platform wiring

Both apps import `@app-template/ui/global.css`. Do not add `tailwind.config.js` or `nativewind/babel`.

- **Web:** PostCSS via `@tailwindcss/postcss` (`apps/admin-web/postcss.config.js`, `apps/client-web/postcss.config.js`). `next.config.mjs` transpiles `nativewind`, `react-native-css`, `@gluestack-ui/*` and defines `__DEV__` for RN-web SSR. No `@gluestack/ui-next-adapter`.
- **Mobile:** Metro uses `withNativewind` from `nativewind/metro` with `input` pointing to `packages/ui/global.css`. Babel uses `babel-preset-expo` only (no NativeWind babel plugin). Rebuild dev client after native/Metro config changes.

Types: `react-native-css-env.d.ts` in each app (not `nativewind-env.d.ts`).

## Web + react-native-web

- Shared screens transpile via `next.config.mjs` (`transpilePackages`, `react-native-web` alias).
- Do not import `@counseliq/ui`, `@counseliq/admin`, or `@counseliq/client` in Server Components without a `'use client'` boundary.
